Lidl has a number of offers in the middle aisle every week – called the Middle of Lidl. From BBQs to fitness gear, and scuba-diving equipment to weighted blankets – there are always some great deals to be found. But what does the legendary middle aisle have in store of Lidl shoppers this week? Here are our top picks. You’ll be able to get your hands on some discounted tech – including wireless headphones and a laptop – at Lidl this week, as well as fishing gear and garden toys. It’s rare to find a laptop under £200, but this Asus Chromebook is just £119.99 at Lidl this week, Designed for durability, it’s got an all-round rubber bumper, spill-resistant keyboard, and ultratough I/O ports – making it ideal for kids or for use on the go. Available in Lidl stores from today. Keen anglers can get their hands on various Crivit fishing tools if they hit the middle aisles, including this net and rod rest priced at £14.99. It’s lightweight for easy travelling, with four detachable rod rests and a rubberised net to snag your catch of the day. Available in Lidl stores from today. At just £19.99, these Bluetooth headphones are a steal. The rechargeable case allows you to power up the earbuds 1.5 times without plugging them in, and they include an integrated microphone for calling. Available in Lidl stores from today. Get your garden ready for spring at Lidl this week, with this Sportspower swing reduced from £79.99 to £69.99. As well as two swings it comes with a glider that seats two, and ground anchors are included so you can keep things extra safe. Available in Lidl stores from Sunday March 13. Follow Metro across our social channels, on Facebook, Twitter and Instagram Share your views in the comments below MORE : Why is popping spots so satisfying and addictive? MORE : Couple who say they haven’t fought in 30 years share their top relationship tips